to the editor anthony lewis is right since the ratification of the bill of rights the federal government has struggled to balance individual civil liberties against the interests of national security op ed feb 24 in times of national crisis like the two world wars as threats to internal security escalated the government 's commitment to preserving individual freedoms declined today the specter of extensive constitutional violations has again been raised we would be well served to remember the words of justice louis d brandeis experience should teach us to be most on our guard to protect liberty when the government 's purposes are beneficent the greatest dangers to liberty lurk in the insidious encroachments of men of zeal well meaning but without understanding suzanne evans berkeley calif feb 24 2003

